## Auth Flow

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Login Page] --> B{Method}
    B -->|Username + Password| C[CredentialsProvider]
    B -->|Google Button| D[GoogleProvider → Google Consent]
    C --> E{Username exists + password matches?}
    E -->|Yes| F[JWT Token]
    E -->|No| G[Error message]
    D --> H[signIn Callback]
    H --> I{Email exists in DB?}
    I -->|Yes| J[Use existing user]
    I -->|No| K[Auto-create as student]
    J --> F
    K --> F
    F --> L[Role-based redirect]
    L -->|admin| M[/admin]
    L -->|teacher| N[/teacher]
    L -->|student| O[/student]
```

## Duplicate Prevention Logic

- **Email is unique**: `email` field has `unique: true` index in MongoDB
- **signIn callback**: Before creating new user, queries `User.findOne({ email })`
- **Cross-provider**: Google user with `test@gmail.com` and OTP user with `test@gmail.com` → same account
- **Username collision**: Auto-increments (`john` → `john1` → `john2` …)

